  "description": "<p>\n\t<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://p1.s.hjfile.cn/thread/201209/2012091414417112_456_o.jpg\" style=\"height: 306px; width: 460px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n\t本节目为沪江部落一档美语发音模仿节目，每期节目选取30秒左右的慢速VOA新闻内容，主持人亲自朗读示范模仿发音，对发音要点进行讲解，并配以详细的语音语调示意图，手把手教你练就地道美音范儿！想要得到主持人专业的点评和意见吗？<a href=\"http://pass.hujiang.com/signup/?source=en_sqyd&amp;url=http://bulo.hujiang.com/menu/11885/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://i2.w.yun.hjfile.cn/doc/201304/d5e293c817a6488d819f0c13a95230e1.jpg\" style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\" /></a>去沪江部落订阅本节目！</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>今日主持人：</strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.8em;\">岩见泽</span></p>\n<p>\n\t30秒音频：<a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p710916\" title=\"点击获得更好的阅读体验\"><img src=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/2009/images/rss_video.gif\" /></a></p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>模仿文本：</strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\"></span><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.8em;\">Not long ago, many people believed that babies only wanted food and to be kept warm and dry. Some people thought babies were not able to learn things until they were five or six months old. But doctors in the United States now say babies begin learning on their first day of life, and even before birth.</span><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.8em;\"></span></p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>译文：</strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\"></span><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.8em;\">就在不久前，许多人还认为婴儿的需求只是食物和温暖干燥的环境。有些人认为婴儿在五、六个月大时才会开始学习，然而美国的医生们则称婴儿们一出生，甚至在出生前便开始学习。</span><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.8em;\"></span></p>\n<p>\n\t<b>小编模仿：</b><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.8em;\"><a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p710916\" title=\"点击获得更好的阅读体验\"><img src=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/2009/images/rss_video.gif\" /></a></span></p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>单词细节：</strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.8em;\"><a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p710916\" title=\"点击获得更好的阅读体验\"><img src=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/2009/images/rss_video.gif\" /></a></span></p>\n<p>\n\t<img src=\"http://i2.w.yun.hjfile.cn/doc/201412/92dad04d243347a6a232f70a69281b15.png\" style=\"height: 204px; width: 460px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n\t◆字母组合 [th]<br />\n\t\\ˈth\\ thought, thing, months, birth, breath<br />\n\t\\ˈth\\ (即\\&eth;\\) that, they, their, bath, breathe</p>\n<p>\n\t◆were \\ˈwər\\<br />\n\twhere \\ˈhwer, ˈwer,(ˈ)(h)wər\\<br />\n\twear \\ˈwer\\</p>\n<p>\n\t◆say \\ˈsā, Southern also ˈse\\<br />\n\tsaying \\ˈsā-iŋ\\<br />\n\tsaid \\ˈsed, especially when subject follows səd\\<br />\n\tsays \\ˈsez, sometimes ˈsāz, especially when subject follows səz\\</p>\n<p>\n\t◆Able \\ˈā-bəl\\ adj.<br />\n\t-able \\-ə-bəl\\<br />\n\tadded to verbs to form adjectives that mean:<br />\n\t1. able to receive the action of the stated verb<br />\n\te.g. breakable, movable, suitable&hellip;.<br />\n\t2. worth receiving the action of the stated verb<br />\n\te.g. an acceptable answer, an admirable person&hellip;.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n\t想要得到主持人专业的点评和意见吗？<a href=\"http://bulo.hujiang.com/menu/11885/item/857518/\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: #f00;\">快来节目现场一试身手吧&gt;&gt;</span></a></p>\n<br /><center><a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p710916/#relate_articles\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_chat.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a> <a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p710916\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_digg.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a></center><h3 style=\"margin: 10px;\">本周最热文章</h3><ul style=\"margin: 5px 0;\"><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p720594/\">四六级查分，你魔性了吗？</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p587662/\">每天要问自己的5个问题 你的答案是什么？</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p720237/\">不运动就能瘦 每天多吃些浆果吧！ </a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p710048/\">外媒看中国 屌丝是什么能吃吗？</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href